   <p1><h2>Description of Makkah's beauty</h2>
    "It is a dream of every obedient servant of Allah to spend at least once in a lifetime experience in this beautiful land, Makkah". 
    "The most beautiful, blessed, wonderful place in the world is Makkah". 
    "No words can do justice to describe how unique this place truly". 
    "You can not express your feelings of visiting Kaaba, you cry when you see the grandeur of the structure". </p1><br>
   <p2><h2>Significance of Makkah</h2>
    Makkah is the holiest city for Muslims.
    It is the birthplace of Prophet Muhammad.
    It is home to Masjid Al Haram (the Great Mosque) and the Kaaba, the qiblah for Muslims to which they turn in their prayers.
    Visiting Makkah to perform Hajj or Umrah is a yearning of Muslims.</p2><br>
    <p3><h2>Why visit Makkah?</h2>
    Some say that visiting Makkah makes them feel closer to God and peaceful. Others say that it is a blessing to visit a place where worshippers from every nation come to worship the one and only God. </p3><br>
